46	{"act": "IT_ACT_2000", "title": "Time of Receipt of Electronic Record", "doc_id": "ITACT_SEC_13_SUB_2", "topics": ["electronic_records", "receipt", "procedure"], "entities": ["addressee", "originator"], "keywords": ["receipt", "electronic record", "designated computer resource", "addressee", "retrieval", "time of receipt"], "metadata": {"act": "IT_ACT_2000", "year": 2000, "jurisdiction": "India"}, "references": [], "clause_text": "Save as otherwise agreed between the originator and the addressee, the time of receipt of an electronic record shall be determined as follows, namely:— (a) if the addressee has designated a computer resource for the purpose of receiving electronic records,— (i) receipt occurs at the time when the electronic record enters the designated computer resource; or (ii) if the electronic record is sent to a computer resource of the addressee that is not the designated computer resource, receipt occurs at the time when the electronic record is retrieved by the addressee; (b) if the addressee has not designated a computer resource along with specified timings, if any, receipt occurs when the electronic record enters the computer resource of the addressee.", "source_files": [1], "conflict_notes": [], "retrieval_text": "Section 13(2) of the Information Technology Act 2000. The time of receipt of an electronic record is determined by whether the addressee has designated a computer resource for receiving records. If a resource is designated, receipt occurs on entry into that resource. If sent to a non-designated resource, receipt occurs on retrieval by the addressee. If no resource is designated, receipt occurs on entry into the addressee's computer resource.", "section_number": "13", "subsection_number": "2", "validation_status": "validated", "plain_english_summary": "Unless agreed otherwise, receipt occurs when the record enters the addressee's designated computer resource, or when retrieved if sent to an undesignated resource. If no resource is designated, receipt occurs upon entry into the addressee's computer resource."}	[0.21179986,0.72173584,-3.8867483,-1.4452342,1.0677562,0.203394,0.6894168,0.80239457,0.58193886,0.39905694,-0.30195877,0.5128257,0.719459,-0.15291093,0.39906865,-0.7376336,0.89366263,-0.35095757,-0.53456384,1.1218933,1.0673906,-0.7554547,-2.3639712,-0.14509566,0.37607974,-0.24294572,0.8358124,0.015701693,-0.6505756,-0.84009194,0.52888435,0.006118901,0.6919392,-0.35805625,-1.1762364,-1.2557174,-0.16736855,-1.1333404,-0.6532568,0.046717312,0.6977214,0.099930964,-0.32440674,0.16964978,0.62754136,0.92258066,0.5984626,0.73404336,0.48859978,0.39002794,0.6177633,-0.5002239,-1.1980253,0.14631411,0.8636659,-0.18452886,-0.6725733,0.34928936,0.4247934,-0.13201655,2.495758,1.5280294,-0.30920035,1.769153,1.524127,-0.072126046,0.40346935,1.1052909,-0.074773796,-0.8097904,0.7453121,-0.120837204,0.06579749,-0.4021106,0.5869269,-0.11949754,-1.1780862,-0.84858567,-0.3611496,1.348445,0.30157542,-0.041163832,1.1296192,0.078075096,0.3993092,0.8531589,0.014904424,0.008026777,0.4202386,1.51885,0.24893016,-0.35045037,0.979404,-0.08313927,-1.2782463,0.9638187,0.07289231,0.13456492,-0.8702589,-0.042087287,-0.66722757,-0.80198646,-0.06365718,-0.8375757,1.5121877,0.89008296,-0.5554056,0.2103955,-0.7279789,-0.34869105,0.3327698,0.51822025,-0.5455101,0.2886074,0.7618132,0.35520864,1.2195324,-0.48401368,-0.49829158,1.0676236,-0.012966422,-0.4225911,-0.81227493,1.0812056,-0.55829066,0.39337873,-0.42458856,0.38665193,0.39329657,0.57483,-0.85450286,-0.39522833,-0.43708715,0.11571696,-0.015571431,-0.045743346,0.12774533,-0.3339458,0.0516916,0.5859038,1.0733203,-0.23642226,-0.09905792,-0.6756454,-0.23816928,0.1140857,0.82190806,-0.29973143,-0.47226042,0.27434853,-1.2355106,-0.021204513,-0.5409743,0.03061106,0.35856056,-0.5649588,0.10023868,-0.13990174,0.6632016,0.83944714,1.361744,0.38136318,-1.5128664,1.0244591,-0.825484,-1.2013495,-0.22760995,-0.22205201,0.39996973,-0.6771448,-0.22509703,-0.15899664,-0.6333644,-0.44469208,