111	{"act": "IT_ACT_2000", "title": "Rule-Making Powers of Central Government", "doc_id": "ITACT_SEC_87_SUB_2", "topics": ["governance", "rule_making", "procedure"], "entities": ["Central Government"], "keywords": ["rule-making", "Central Government", "electronic signature", "security procedures", "intermediary guidelines", "CERT-In", "adjudicating officer"], "metadata": {"act": "IT_ACT_2000", "year": 2000, "jurisdiction": "India"}, "references": ["ITACT_SEC_67C", "ITACT_SEC_69", "ITACT_SEC_69A", "ITACT_SEC_69B", "ITACT_SEC_70", "ITACT_SEC_70B", "ITACT_SEC_79"], "clause_text": "In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: the conditions for reliability of electronic signature; manner of authentication; electronic form for government filings; manner of service charges for service providers; type, manner and format of electronic signature; security procedures and practices; qualifications of adjudicating officers; information retention and preservation under section 67C; procedures for interception, monitoring or decryption under sections 69, 69A, 69B; information security for protected systems; functions of CERT-In; and guidelines for intermediaries under section 79.", "source_files": [1], "conflict_notes": [], "retrieval_text": "Section 87(2) of the Information Technology Act 2000. The Central Government's rule-making power covers: reliability conditions for electronic signatures; authentication procedures; electronic form for government filings; service provider charges; electronic signature type, manner and format; security procedures; adjudicating officer qualifications; information retention by intermediaries under section 67C; procedures and safeguards for interception, monitoring and decryption under sections 69, 69A, 69B; information security practices for protected systems under section 70; functions of CERT-In under section 70B; and guidelines for intermediaries under section 79.", "section_number": "87", "subsection_number": "2", "validation_status": "validated", "plain_english_summary": "The Central Government may make rules covering electronic signature reliability, authentication procedures, e-governance filings, security practices, adjudication procedures, data retention by intermediaries, surveillance safeguards, and intermediary guidelines, among other matters."}	[0.13464986,1.1684718,-3.32765,-0.89306355,1.2971872,0.24123998,-0.62838876,0.98846966,0.71233445,-0.25916636,-0.06369247,0.34154016,0.3154063,-0.79094005,0.42339483,-0.38610232,0.67373294,-1.0448543,0.10834936,0.4414434,0.6485018,-1.2734385,-1.2924464,0.103674635,1.2574906,-0.3402703,1.3681326,-0.71305335,-1.1748663,-1.6849792,1.2198777,-0.26602337,1.3079586,-0.6849032,-0.5872638,-1.5951818,0.8620553,0.40808052,-0.8684985,0.37030363,1.2393287,0.113253824,-0.27870986,-0.39231366,0.06814568,0.14389877,0.9250365,0.15519267,-0.0455589,-0.67187893,0.004690305,-0.9088335,0.4801679,-0.46353337,1.0253834,0.32908863,-1.1404307,0.62921536,0.094911724,-0.7885586,1.4681171,0.98770493,-1.1915576,0.8482616,0.20620798,-0.77555674,-0.047355637,1.4594508,-0.22682293,-0.083841875,0.5937919,-0.11631795,0.7027638,-0.58872986,0.5451083,-1.0020934,-0.7682341,-0.7476586,0.38518214,1.1098348,0.078295134,-0.64976865,1.4516468,0.16078559,0.43742967,0.24687293,-0.74622756,-0.5153296,0.45064375,1.8069495,0.081721246,-0.5734158,0.6990382,-0.5463797,-0.39777002,0.2963064,0.88613594,-0.22419588,-0.13245595,-0.33157244,-0.5230208,-1.0537949,0.26621002,-0.08563371,0.20109561,1.2297895,-0.021762589,-0.5279541,-0.9204089,0.23146847,0.11344148,1.0391463,-0.15706857,0.08855837,0.29902315,0.67230016,0.9694365,-0.89631677,0.25505975,0.5904212,-0.4998977,-0.99160486,-0.090170816,0.33381596,0.26175728,-0.44059512,-0.77517396,0.081351966,-0.1538875,-0.92742664,-0.15372068,0.3516109,-0.82277495,-0.2631162,0.4435874,0.8289534,-0.5436296,-0.85336304,0.045577407,-0.1338016,0.5663663,0.3236197