113	{"act": "IT_ACT_2000", "title": "Documents or Transactions Excluded from the Act", "doc_id": "ITACT_FIRST_SCHEDULE", "topics": ["exemption", "excluded_documents", "scope"], "entities": [], "keywords": ["First Schedule", "excluded documents", "negotiable instrument", "power of attorney", "trust", "will", "immovable property", "exemption"], "metadata": {"act": "IT_ACT_2000", "year": 2000, "jurisdiction": "India"}, "references": ["ITACT_SEC_1_SUB_4"], "clause_text": "Documents or transactions to which the Act shall not apply: 1. A negotiable instrument (other than a cheque) as defined in section 13 of the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881. 2. A power-of-attorney as defined in section 1A of the Powers-of-Attorney Act, 1882. 3. A trust as defined in section 3 of the Indian Trust Act, 1882. 4. A will as defined in clause (h) of section 2 of the Indian Succession Act, 1925, including any other testamentary disposition by whatever name called. 5. Any contract for the sale or conveyance of immovable property or any interest in such property.", "source_files": [1], "conflict_notes": [], "retrieval_text": "First Schedule to the Information Technology Act 2000. Lists documents and transactions to which the Act does not apply: negotiable instruments (excluding cheques) under the Negotiable Instruments Act 1881; powers of attorney under the Powers-of-Attorney Act 1882; trusts under the Indian Trust Act 1882; wills and testamentary dispositions under the Indian Succession Act 1925; and contracts for the sale or conveyance of immovable property or any interest therein.", "section_number": "First Schedule", "subsection_number": null, "validation_status": "validated", "plain_english_summary": "The First Schedule lists documents and transactions excluded from the Act: negotiable instruments (other than cheques), powers of attorney, trusts, wills and testamentary dispositions, and contracts for sale or conveyance of immovable property."}	[0.2461224,0.37794802,-2.8566914,-0.26633853,