159	{"act": "IT_ACT_2000", "title": "Punishment for Sending Offensive Messages [Struck Down]", "doc_id": "ITACT_SEC_66A", "topics": ["cyber_offence", "penalty"], "entities": [], "keywords": ["offensive messages", "section 66A", "Shreya Singhal", "struck down", "unconstitutional", "freedom of speech", "computer resource", "communication device"], "metadata": {"act": "IT_ACT_2000", "year": 2000, "jurisdiction": "India"}, "references": [], "clause_text": "Any person who sends, by means of a computer resource or a communication device,— (a) any information that is grossly offensive or has menacing character; or (b) any information which he knows to be false, but for the purpose of causing annoyance, inconvenience, danger, obstruction, insult, injury, criminal intimidation, enmity, hatred or ill will, persistently by making use of such computer resource or a communication device; (c) any electronic mail or electronic mail message for the purpose of causing annoyance or inconvenience or to deceive or to mislead the addressee or recipient about the origin of such messages, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and with fine.", "source_files": [1], "conflict_notes": [], "retrieval_text": "Section 66A of the Information Technology Act 2000. This section criminalised sending grossly offensive or menacing information, knowingly false information causing annoyance or ill will, and deceptive electronic messages using computer resources or communication devices, with punishment of imprisonment up to three years and fine. The Supreme Court of India struck down section 66A in Shreya Singhal v. Union of India, AIR 2015 SC 1523, as unconstitutional for violating the right to freedom of speech and expression under Article 19(1)(a) of the Constitution.", "section_number": "66A", "subsection_number": null, "validation_status": "validated", "plain_english_summary": "Section 66A penalised sending grossly offensive, menacing, or false messages through computer resources or communication devices. This section was struck down by the Supreme Court of India in Shreya Singhal v. Union of India (2015) as unconstitutional."}	[1.6771691,0.88248146,-2.7603705,-0.03525775,0.8747428,0.24819095,-0.10677308,1.0583134,0.071475126,0.51330453,0.52041197,0.7036005,1.081712,-0.34054884,0.31149063,-0.6152884,0.33598632,-0.8169031,-0.8991706,0.6419568,0.13808872,0.33451307,-1.4268507,-0.6377011,1.3739209,-0.4414088,1.0998509,0.11808894,-0.5158126,0.17443557,1.1278043,0.08390118,0.41624257,-0.35398108,-0.93112636,-0.91383135,0.5843635,0.05186088,-1.024291,-0.7254666,1.2544332,0.13257802,-0.92462146,-0.5034676,0.44431666,-0.102771096,0.8207709,0.075325854,0.8951303,-0.66738856,0.18852141,-1.6158597,0.39402312,-1.2737055,0.3386941,0.57700676,-1.3502005,-0.12603836,-0.21266654,0.52925885,0.7142577,0.9892153,-1.3400662,0.9598021,0.9170617,-0.17334804,-0.050519463,1.049695,-0.47629216,-0.9317377,1.6041881,-0.905286,0.21265294,0.45421407,-0.074738786,-0.5226071,-0.3281066,-0.7762008,-0.15472358,0.9361975,0.18953142,-0.61165404,1.0927366,-0.023849593,0.3204082,-0.56590265,-0.636292,-0.19809783,-0.26670918,1.3062109,0.08221599,0.14735404,0.2488813,0.040117897,-0.49452755,-0.5577525,-0.09416541,-0.1898962,-0.67603314,0.2106455,-0.08836545,-0.65046996,0.73434305,-0.4330077,0.28476307,0.55339426,0.4504708,-1.1826907,-0.6652788,-0.5637823,0.44495875,0.59620893,-0.30506426,-0.42354065,0.86155766,0.37714946,1.4766632,-1.5426847,0.008306042,-0.17297481,-0.03696249,0.0043340307,-0.43342444,0.34551275,0.69950676,-0.17576292,-0.53282005,0.20860976,0.07064015,-1.5321851,-0.82830656,0.011441966,-0.8352974,-0.13053054,0.26842642,0.4427122,0.107491724,-0.47540933,-0.18835387,-0.33368906,0.8422086,-0.3464873,0.44626364,0.011121721,0.51941895,-0.85643077,0.67698944,-0.2648021,-0.31756786,0.19685538,-0.94427824,0.33518487,0.86042434,-0.14729771,-0.051261548,-0.99933314,0.3746538,0.77581203,0.24408776,0.030490037,0.8999912,0.9928134,0.14712405,1.9557279,