202	{"act": "SPDI_RULES_2011", "title": "Disclosure of Information - Prior Consent Requirement", "doc_id": "SPDI_RULE_6_SUB_1", "topics": ["disclosure", "consent", "sensitive_personal_data"], "entities": ["body corporate", "Government agency"], "keywords": ["disclosure", "third party", "prior permission", "body corporate", "lawful contract", "legal obligation", "Government agency", "written request", "cyber incidents", "investigation"], "metadata": {"act": "SPDI_RULES_2011", "year": 2011, "jurisdiction": "India"}, "references": ["SPDI_RULE_3"], "clause_text": "Disclosure of sensitive personal data or information by body corporate to any third party shall require prior permission from the provider of such information, who has provided such information under lawful contract or otherwise, unless such disclosure has been agreed to in the contract between the body corporate and provider of information, or where the disclosure is necessary for compliance of a legal obligation: Provided that the information shall be shared, without obtaining prior consent from provider of information, with Government agencies mandated under the law to obtain information including sensitive personal data or information for the purpose of verification of identity, or for prevention, detection, investigation including cyber incidents, prosecution, and punishment of offences. The Government agency shall send a request in writing to the body corporate possessing the sensitive personal data or information stating clearly the purpose of seeking such information. The Government agency shall also state that the information so obtained shall not be published or shared with any other person.", "source_files": [2], "conflict_notes": [], "retrieval_text": "Rule 6(1) of the SPDI Rules 2011 requires a body corporate to obtain prior permission from the information provider before disclosing sensitive personal data or information to any third party, unless the disclosure was agreed in the original contract or is necessary for a legal obligation. An exception exists for Government agencies mandated by law to obtain sensitive personal data for identity verification, prevention, detection, investigation of cyber incidents, prosecution and punishment of offences. Such agencies must send a written request stating the purpose and confirming the information will not be published or shared further.", "section_number": "6", "subsection_number": "1", "validation_status": "validated", "plain_english_summary": "Disclosing sensitive personal data to a third party requires prior consent from the information provider, unless agreed in contract or required by legal obligation. Government agencies may obtain such data without prior consent for identity verification, investigation, or prosecution, but must submit a written request stating the purpose and undertaking not to publish or further share the information."}	[0.8623761,0.9474893,-2.954388,0.3888988,0.07064139,0.07902444,-0.29650003,0.26939142,0.32262507,0.49654582,0.022173584,0.60699713,0.1716403,-0.42386752,0.07421714,-0.21352886,0.5857836,-1.2710758,-0.555796,0.7391544,-0.43404898,-0.1533799,-1.4049913,0.24713443,1.2176238,-0.49299437,1.2883676,-1.0702446,-0.25945663,-0.47405282,0.7504622,0.9074916,0.2168912,-0.5332985,-0.44276142,-1.9741874,0.24591327,0.08776108,-1.9980087,0.610934,0.8157615,0.21364737,-0.52291006,-0.9733835,0.4679102,-0.33853292,0.9696012,-0.10131606,1.1033103,-1.4827887,1.0212129,-0.3831525,-0.30060488,-0.5256265,0.71313924,0.03529248,-0.3235675,-0.44107407,0.18336059,-1.2802014,1.6808624,1.3261503,-0.5407307,1.136731,0.8542853,-0.14455648,-0.9722152,0.69781744,-0.23343347,-0.6686353,0.91763055,0.18212555,0.6564577,-0.32023084,0.5380419,-0.49575654,-0.6829043,-1.0291529,0.33156395,0.4503253,1.1557205,0.17381129,1.1404357,0.7128856,0.7136721,0.66227454,-0.35068807,-0.42959264,0.29410696,1.4890655,0.6914627,-0.38850588,0.9198089,-0.17897727,-0.2781122,0.8357603,0.04636933,0.27985656,-0.7061795,-0.17720585,-