219	{"act": "CERTIN_DIRECTIONS_2022", "title": "Format for Point of Contact Information Submission to CERT-In", "doc_id": "CERTIN_ANNEXURE_2", "topics": ["contact_management", "compliance", "cybersecurity"], "entities": ["CERT-In", "service provider", "intermediary", "data centre", "body corporate", "Government organisation"], "keywords": ["Point of Contact", "PoC", "format", "info@cert-in.org.in", "designation", "organisation", "email ID", "mobile number", "Annexure II"], "metadata": {"act": "CERTIN_DIRECTIONS_2022", "year": 2022, "jurisdiction": "India"}, "references": ["CERTIN_DIR_3", "ITACT_SEC_70B"], "clause_text": "Format for providing Point of Contact (PoC) information by Service providers, intermediaries, data centres, body corporate and Government organisations to CERT-In. The Information relating to the Point of Contact shall be sent to CERT-In via email (info@cert-in.org.in) in the format specified below and shall be updated from time to time: Name; Designation; Organisation Name; Office Address; Email ID; Mobile No.; Office Phone; Office Fax.", "source_files": [3], "conflict_notes": [], "retrieval_text": "Annexure II to the CERT-In Directions 2022 prescribes the format for providing Point of Contact information to CERT-In as required by Direction (iii). Service providers, intermediaries, data centres, body corporates and government organisations must submit their designated Point of Contact details via email to info@cert-in.org.in. The required details include the PoC's name, designation, organisation name, office address, email ID, mobile number, office phone number, and office fax number. This information must be kept updated from time to time.", "section_number": "Annexure II", "subsection_number": null, "validation_status": "validated", "plain_english_summary": "Annexure II prescribes the format for submitting Point of Contact information to CERT-In. Covered entities must provide the PoC's name, designation, organisation name, office address, email I